column5: Took a while to find the camera.. so didnt' get a shot until it was a good 400 feet from the dining room window. Walked right across the front yard.. size of a horse. This is probably the little guy Marty came up out of the bush babbling about last year.. lol. All he could get out is I didn't think they came that big...    Terrible zoom/crop.. but look at the height of that rack above his head..
Yer an    man.    LOL   Thats a beast.

Ok Wayne, not sure the deal you have with the other hunters there, but I'll make ya a deal.  Let me have 2 days of bowhunting and in return I'll give you 5 years worth of personal fishing journals in the Sturgeon bay and honey harbour area for Muskie, walleye, pike, crappie and LMB/SMB.  I'll even take the last week in Dec.  Deal??
hey back off.LOL  Marty will have him in the Dec shotgun hunt,wont ya Marty,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Marty WAKE UP.
But did you catch anything Phil???  Marty and Brian have first dibs... but you never know they may work you in or give you a spot on the 120...
See I told you if you planted the landing strip with Orchard grass you would have a lot of friends Wayne.   Art

Haha, just kidding around Wayne. I respect other hunters property. However, that is a nice animal you have there.  To answer the fish question....ya we did, but not a lot of muskie info. Then again, a fresh set of eyes on a property could maybe change the luck up a little
That's a nice buck for sure. I have a couple that size hanging around close to home as well. Just haven't got around to paying them a visit yet.
I feal a cough coming on.Is it Friday yet?
Nicely done Wayne...I should've never doubted you LOL  That's a beast indeed!
